caption: Terrible customer service. The man that took our order barely said two words to us and looked bothered that we were even there. He didn’t even call us when our food was ready. Staff were great, but unfortunately my meal experience was not so great. I ordered the okra gumbo in a to-go container and by the time I made it home, the rice container sitting on top of the gumbo container broke through the gumbo container plastic lid. This caused the gumbo to leak out into the plastic bag the container was in. It was a mess. Plastic shards from the gumbo container lid were soaked into the gumbo remaining in its styrofoam container. I painstakingly picked out the plastic pieces I could from the meal (probably didn't get all of them) and tried the gumbo. After all that, gumbo was mediocre, and needed more salt.  I encourage Meals From The Heart Cafe to reconsider their packaging so no one else has to go through this disappointing experience. In fact having compostable or recyclable packaging and limiting their use of single use plastics would make me more willing to give the place another try. It is important to me that the eating establishments I support are socially and environmentally responsible.

While visiting nola we decided to order some food at Meals from the heart cafe. We were very impressed with the variety of vegan options and super excited to eat there. It is at a very busy place, but they have an effective way of telling that your order is ready by SMS message, while you can easily explore the market. 30 min after our order, we got the message and, when we got there, unfortunately another family had mistakenly taken our food some minutes before we got there. Of course we were quite upset with this event, BUT the worker (I'm so sorry I didn't get his name :( ) was SO kind and he politely apologized for it , refunded our order (even though I insisted we were okay) , and he and the cook team worked on our "re-order" immediately. Long story short: we got our delicious meal 15 min after that, for free, and with an incredible experience of human kindness! Definitely recommend the place! Most importantly: food is delicious!

Meals From the Heart has a great mission to serve familiar Southern favorites in a healthy wholesome way. It's a family owned restaurant where grandma's recipes are sure to please! Everything is homemade and made to order in the small on-site kitchen. Their specialties are crabcakes and plant-based meals with plenty of vegan and gluten-free options.  In addition to everything being so fresh and healthy - and homemade, we really appreciated that Meals From the Heart was able to accommodate everyone's dietary preferences and restrictions. I had the crab cake tacos - also enough for two, but it was so good I devoured it all myself!  We highly recommend Meals From the Heart! This is a definite destination point when in the French Quarter Market. Family owned and black owned, the food is excellent, tasty, and healthy home cooking. We spoke with the two waiters, who were relatives, who said that their grandmother is the major cook with the recipes whose goal from the gitgo was to provide healthy food and that she does. Low sodium, no pork, no transfat with veg and vegan food as well as carne dishes. Had the crab cake po boys, which took me back to my childhood eating at the kitchen table at my grandparents' home. So authentic, not that fake crab meat. Even had tiny bit of shell to prove its real crab. And the amount of crab was huge. Two people can share a PO boy. The vegan gluten free gumbo was divine too!!!And what I neglected to add was that their politics are spot on. The purpose of this joint is to provide healthy food to stop black people from dying of bad food. You just can't go wrong with this place. They may open a second location for the locals, so fingers crossed. Go there NOW!!

I gave this place five stars, because it met the basics -- does the staff and owner look like the city? Yes. Was it open when I arrived? Yes. So, they get a five, because I want to see them prosper. Most of you won't read the reviews any way. So, I have some notes for the owner -- 20-25 minutes to get ready is too long. It's too hot for all that. Figure out how to decrease your time. Perhaps reduce your menu. Figure out how to make it fresh and quick. Especially, since you only have 7 seats. Get them fed and on their way. You should be offering water to all who are ordering. You had 3 people working the front and it still took two minutes to get acknowledged after I picked up the menu myself and made a decision 3 minutes ago. So, it took five minutes to get acknowledged. I don't understand why you ran out of carrot juice so early in the day. But I guess that's also a good sign. I had the shake and it was delicious. I was expecting it to take more time, but the waitress said they just made a batch. I say you go all the way with the heart healthy and add earth healthy by using 100% paper cups and lids and utensils. Good luck and best wishes.

There is nothing that isn't delicious. You don't need to be vegan to enjoy this amazing soul food. Get the ma and cheese and the sweet potatos... And a bit of everything else!

The dinner portions are huge! We could have cut our bill in half by ordering a half portion for each of us. They surprised me by making a gluten free po'boy that was tasty and didn't just crumble. The menu was a bit misleading because crawfisb was listed as a GF option even though it really wasn't, but the staff knew to help me when I ordered and steered me to the shrimp which actually was gluten free. The meal came with a side salad that had a good mix of veggies and nearly half of an avacado. It took a bit to get the order out, but to me that shows that it was made fresh.

I wasn't sure what vegan options we would find in the French Quarter market, but this place was divine! They even have a little bar where you can sit, but we found a larger table in the common area.  Their pancakes looked wonderful but we opted for a sandwich. Was not disappointed!
Vegan crab cakes are delicious and the staff was delightful!

The gf crab cakes were bomb, prices for tourists and not worth getting the gf po boy option (which just throws some store bought bread on there). Overall it was filling (for two) and very expensive but fun to sit and eat in the market.
Food was amazing! We went two days in a row because they had excellent healthy options and it's tough to get a good healthy meal here! Great service and food!

I went because i wanted to try an Impossible Burger. However they cooked it so long that it negated the advantages of the burger. The custeomer service was friendly but very slow. There were five people in the cook's area but it took 30 minutes to make a burger and crab cakes. The spouse said the crab cakes were not good. So... Meh.

Absolutely fantastic food. Very friendly family that owns and operates this place. The food is made to order but the vegan food only takes like 10 minutes. The vegan crab cake po-boy is so good that I had it three times over the course of my 5 day stay in New Orleans. I cannot recommend this place enough.

AMAZING vegan food!!! Crab cake po-boy is so so good! Highly recommend, food is made to order so expect 15-20 min wait. Great family business and such good tasting vegan options. I’m very impressed (:
One of my favorite places in town! Many vegan options!
Vegan Gumbo is so good!
So delicious! Great if you gave food allergies. Very accommodating!
Best grits in the world

It's so hard to get vegetarian food in New Orleans. This place is perfect! I went there multiple times in two days and I got the  Vegan Po Boy, it was very crunchy and delicious! I wowed to.go there everytime I visit New Orleans.

I've been to this place before and in the past the service was remarkable. Today I ordered a crab cake and a Vegan sausage and it took 45 minutes to get the order. In the midst of me waiting i watched 2 different groups of people sit, order, get their food, and leave. They ordered the same thing I did. When I brought this to the servers attention, she told.me the food is made from scratch and takes a long time. I've waited 20 minutes before and been happy to do it, but 45 minutes is ridiculous. The server had green hair and lipstick but I didnt get her name. She was VERY rude. I wont be back if I see her there.

Wonderful Vegetarian / Vegan Options .. They make everything fresh. The Market concept brigs out the street food feel . Must try Vegetarian Crab Cake - I didn't realize Artichokes can be transformed in such a way! The other thing we tried was the Vegetarian Gumbo.. Yummmm!!!
Wholesome hole in the wall crab cake variations with out door market flare.
Good food and caring service. Food made with love.  It's good.

I had the passion salad with a crab cake. The crab cake was delicious. The salad was as basic as it gets, no frills, mixed greens and two sliced tomatoes. There is not great value with this place as portions are small for the price BUT the taste of the crab cakes again were delicious. I would  return and most likely get the crab cake poboy (albeit more expensive but   I will leave with a sense of satiety at least).

They ask about food allergies; where else in the world does that happen??? They're patient and take the time to attend to you while you decide what you're ordering.  Seated in the heart of the French Market, this place needs a TRUE STOREFRONT... I'd be there weekly.  They have pressed juice. Pricing is great.  The food is made fresh and in-front your face (actually just behind a door) but you're able to see the cooks and there's nothing sketchy going on.  Converting to a non-meat eating & non-dairy eater is challenging and this place and a few others make it all the easier.  My only regret is that: I ATE IT ALL in ONE SETTING; it was soooooo delicious that I shamefully ate it all.  I wanted to save some for later, but it was just too good and I didn't have a full feeling, although I know you shouldn't eat until FULL, but hey I did it anyway... so I continued to eat until it was gone.  The staff was patient and kind.  I knew a few of them were in training, but the trainer was patient and pointed out obvious errors in a loving manner.  My food was prepared to my likening and in a swift, but in a knowingly FRESHLY PREPARED way.  Additionally, once i devoured all the food on my plate, I didn't have a full, stuffed, can't move feeling.  I was refreshed and still felt light and fluffy, which made walking back to my car all the easier.  Parking wasn't easy, but it was worth it!!!!!!
It was just ok
A must every time we come to New Orleans. Probably the only healthy meal I eat while I'm here! Always delicious!
Awesome vegan crab tacos
My hotel recommended this place and they didn’t let me down!! Really fun brunch place that ties in seafood. Love how it’s in the market too- great people watching.

It's hard to find allergy-friendly food in the Quarter, especially gluten-free and allergy-friendly. Meals From the Heart delivers. No pork products, tons of gluten-free, vegan/vegetarian options, and all of it is delicious, value for money, and fresh as can be. We go here for breakfast every day we're in New Orleans, and it's a delight every time.
Have been here many times and always have a great meal. The crab cakes are worth the wait!
Long wait for the food. Took about half an hour to arrive
So much attention to detail. Quality of food, friendliness of staff.....it doesn't get a lot better.
Love love love this place! I ate there twice in my short trip to NOLA.

Lots of vegan options, including mind-blowing pancakes and awesome fake crab cakes. Counter staff were friendly and helpful. Counter space is limited in French market, prices are reasonable for the area.

The vegan food here is amazing! The 'crab' cakes are my favorite. Thanks for having such great options for us vegans. Most importantly, the staff was very friendly and is passionate about what they're doing.
Amazing vegan food options and outstanding staff.
This place was SO DELICIOUS. I had the vegan po boy and my husband had the crab cakes. "Best crab cakes I've ever had" he said. Very friendly staff, everything made fresh to order. Highly recommend.
Great place for vegans. Food is always excellent.
Came here with my girlfriend and the food was some of the best tasting food I had. Definitely coming back for seconds when I come back into town! Great for conversation too!  Overall, try the 🦀
Multiple great vegan options and friendly service!  Highly recommend the black beans soup, mushroom po'boy could have used more mushrooms but was delicious and served with a super yummy sauce!
Amazing food; amazing service! The vegan Gumbo was unbelievable!
Pancakes were great, I found the salmon and grits very wet but the grits we're good and the salmon cooked well. One if the most expensive places we ate at
DELICIOUS gf options and the staff was amazing! Definitely coming back!!
Had the veggie po- boy. Delicious and fresh! Staff was helpful with describing options. Food is made to order so this is not fast food, but worth the small wait.
My babe and I love this place.
The GF crab cakes are *amazing*!!
Great vegan and vegitarian food.A little pricey.Very friendly staff.
Really loved the vegan crab cake tacos. It's an outdoor cafe in the French Market

Had the gluten free crab cake po boy and it was absolutely fantastic! Plus the staff here was incredibly friendly making Meals from the Heart a complete pleasure to go to. Thanks so much for the great food!
Wait was long, but the mushroom po boy was worth it. OmG good!!
Gluten free crab cake is delicious. Gf okra gumbo is Ok, not great. Gf Cheesy grits are also ok, not great. Their juices are small and pricey. Would stick to the crab cake only next time.
Best vegan crabcakes ever
Food is amazing! Very nice staff too! Totally random stop for food and couldn't have been happier!
Love the vegan options. Absolutely delicious

What a great little family owned shop.  Ms. Avril and the staff there were very polite. And having healthier options was perfect. They described what was being done to ensure clean cooking surfaces for our food.  It is located in the farmers market type corridor among other shops. A neat little atmosphere.  I will recommend this place for sure, especially if you need vegan or gluten free.  Thank you Meals from the Heart.
Dear god, go eat a crab cake immediately!
The crab cake tacos were very tasty.
Omg! Such a gift from the heavens! I'm gluten free vegan and I was so happy (and relieved!) to have found this place!
I am gluten free and I was able to eat with no problem.
Great food...... Great service.... Guilt free nutrition.....
username: Baba Ken Amen aka DJ Dope Amen

caption: Love this place! Had the Vegan Po'boy and the Vegan pancakes and power shake. All were fantastic!
Awful quality photo because I basically couldn't wait to sit down and eat it. And it was deliciousss!

Wait time is VERY long. I get that they make it fresh and all, but its still a little too long for my preference. Don't go if you are hungry or impatient. My wife thinks their vegan gumbo was good, but I thought the Food is allrite.
The vegan food was way too expensive. The wait to get my order filled was way too long. The taste was edible at best.
Oh dear!   These pancakes are the devil himself.   :).  Great service.   Cool location.   Trying to lose weight...   best choice I could pick to eat.   :0).  Thank you all.

Less than 1 star. Soup microwaved that wasn't prepared until 25 minutes after patiently waiting and inquiring the status 3 times... Multiple other parties were served after ordering quite some time after us. And it was not even remotely busy. Assumed kaepernick jersey "boss" had no interest in serving a very kind patient patron of local businesses who even tipped (my fiancee). This was round Christmas 2017... Edit: He seemed to be actively engaged in managing the restaurant with no interest whatsoever in communicating or serving our fiancee. Did not in the slightest definition seem to be "Passing by"...

Unbelievably friendly staff, manager, and food is over the top delicious!! This is our 2nd visit in 2 days, and we’re coming back tomorrow before our flight. Had vegan pancakes, sausage, shake, burger, sandwich so far!! WOW!!! Make sure you try this place!

We visited this cafe twice on our honeymoon. I did as much research as I could before visiting the city because I knew it would be difficult as a vegan to find meals I could eat. I was so incredibly excited to visit a cafe that shared my values. It was fantastic both times!! The service is amazing, friendly and helpful. The first time my husband had the famous vegan crab cake tacos, wow!! And I had the beyond Burger with the potatoes and it was amazing! On our second visit I had the vegan blueberry pancakes topped with more blueberries, strawberries and nuts. Omg They were the best I have ever had. Seriously I cannot say enough about them. My husband had the poached eggs and crab cakes on an English muffin. And they were fantastic. Thank you so much!! And if you are ever looking to open another location, please come to Canada!!

Hi, My son and I ate late at the cafe yesterday. We both had the impossible burger, one vegan and one veggie. Served with potatoes. Total $43. The burger was substandard in every way. I have eaten alot of IB from all over the states. This one looked as if it had been cut in half,  stood on, fed to the dog, collected then shared between the buns. My son and I felt cheated in every way.. Never again will I visit your establishment, you should consider renaming your business as nothing whatsoever was from the heart.  JRT
Best crab cakes anywhere!  A required NOLA destination for our family!

We ordered the vegan Philly Cheese steak, and they told us it would be ready in 25 minutes. It took over and hour, and 30 minutes before they served us they said it would only be 5 more minutes. The people who ordered after us also had the same problem. When we finally received our food, there was no cheese. When we told them this, they said that there was cheese, and we could not see it because it was melted. No one tasted any cheese because there was none. The food was good, but they lied about the wait and about the cheese. Never eating there again.

Awesome gluten free vegan little restaurant! The food is delicious the server lady is very knowledgeable about food allergy and very careful to serve everybody's needs! She ask if she needs to be aware of any food allergy before they cook the food!!Excellent place I would recommend it to anyone with food allergy!!!
I love all of the fresh ingredients

I love meals from the heart.  I'm pretty vegan so I was delighted to find it. A big surprise was that they have great coffee! Of course the food is great and the people are fun, friendly, and welcoming. You probably guessed that from the other terrific reviews. :-)
Gluten free options and a very friendly staff!

Great menu selection of healthy choices for breakfast and lunch. I had the crab cake tacos and all of the ingredients were super fresh and flavorful. All meals are made to order so the wait is atleast 15 minutes, but definitely worth the wait and price. A 12 oz cold-pressed carrot juice and my tacos was $24. I would highly recommend
Great vegan options in the French Market. Don't miss the vegan crab cake tacos and that Power smoothie.

We had this place marked but didn't realize it was inside the French market building. What a great surprise since that was our first stop in the French quarter and it was about lunch time. The service was as good as the food and it was nice having some vegan Cajun spiced options.

I hate to  give this place such a low rating, but my experience here wasn't  positive. I sat at the counter & ordered a single vegan crab cake slider and a bowl of cheese grits. The total came to $15.14. I thought that was a bit pricey for what I ordered,  but I hoped that the portions  would be decent and the quality would be worth the price. I  waited over 40 minutes  for my food after asking for ETA twice. The woman seated next to me (who was there before me) waited as long or longer for her tacos. When my food finally arrived, I was shocked at how small the portions were. The cheese grits were in a small styrofoam bowl and didn't taste or look like they had any vegan cheese at all.The slider was smaller than I expected and had a "crab cake"  that  was mushy and falling apart. I did eat the slider- which didn't taste bad-, but at a cost of  $8, I felt kinda ripped off.I spoke up about the grits to the young lady working in the front and her solution was that I pay for extra cheese. Before I could tell her that wasn't fair to me, the owner (I believe)intervened and gave me a refund. Again, I wanted to like this place, but the wait time, portions, price and quality would keep me from ever returning here.
Wonderful service! Outstanding food options, especially for those of us who don't eat meat, or shellfish.

This place is an absolute gem, especially for anyone with food allergies.  The gluten-free crab cakes will blow your mind!!  And yes, get them for breakfast -- paired with a perfectly over-easy egg will start your day off right.  They serve Cafe du Monde coffee, so you can get your fix without standing in that line.  Delightful and attentive service, tremendous food, great value!  Best meal of my trip!!
Awesome food. Awesome customer service! They were out of the vegan gumbo, so I guess I'll have to come back to get some! 😊
Good Gluten free pancakes, expect to  wait  twenty to thirty minutes for  your order
slow service.  positive attitudes dont compensate for the food quality and slim pickins.

The Vegan blueberry Pancakes were amazing!!!  worth the wait , but the service was just ok . Look at the menu before you arrive and know what you want when you arrive at the counter.
Fantastic gluten free pancakes!! I had been looking for something different because I was tired of eggs and bacon. The staff was incredibly nice. And did I mention the food is amazing??
Pancakes! Ice coffee! Vegan crab cakes!
New Orleans. Nothing else need to be said GREAT
Great gluten free options!

With aarhs family group, we stopped into the market so everyone could have food options of their choice. I had a crab cake taco!! Highly recommend. Delicious! My friend has sensitive diet concerns and they were accomading to her needs. They also have beyond meat burgers and other vegan options. Also award winning packcakes from travel and leisure magazine.

So good! The staff is great! I am not even a vegan the food is so good we went two days in a row. Considering it’s not a restaurant the place is Soo clean they opened the kitchen door and everything was so organized and Soo clean(please look at the other food places in that market) definitely a go to place and a much healthier alternative. Everything I saw come out that kitchen looks great.Because everything is made to order I suggest order your food walk around the market and come back!
Waiting and waited and waited. No service. No wye contact. Just left. So disappointed as I was looking forward to some vegan food in NOLA.
Beautiful food,drink and people.
Took 45 minutes for food to be ready, and then we both felt sick after eating there

My husband and I are in New Orleans for a week and we visited this spot a few times. Our favorite vegan dish was the vegan crab cake tacos and we tried a non-vegan crab cake as well that was incredible. I also recommend the local kombucha and fresh carrot juice.

This place has got it going on!!!!! Food is incredible!!! Gumbo was so warm and filling 😊👍 amazing drink selection! I wish more restaurants offered kombucha !! Best of all the staff makes you feel at home and very welcomed !!! Thank you so much I won't forget you 💘
I got the crab cake po' boy which was delicious. It was very meaty and I couldn't finish it all! The remoulade was really good.
Vegan crab cake tacos are a MUST HAVE.

I had the vegetarian Gumbo here and it was one of the best Gumbo's I had in New Orleans. The place was a little difficult to find and it's an open counter type of place with limited seating, but the vegetarian Gumbo made it all worth it. Very nice and courteous staff.
Obsessed with their vegan gumbo and gluten free pancakes. If you're a local, be sure to get a loyalty card. Fresh sliced oranges while you wait. Very friendly staff...tip them :)

I was very happy to find a place in The Crescent City that serves gluten-free crab cakes and gumbo, so I made it a point to visit and try their food. They seem to be concerned about food allergies.  All-in-all I can't complain about the taste.  It was pretty good. The main reason they did not get 5 stars is the price. One bowl of gumbo (with very yummy gluten-free toast),  a single crab cake with a small cup of remoulade,  and a kombucha came to a whopping $34! For some that would just be an appetizer and they would still be hungry.  While it was good,  at that price,  I'm not sure how often I'd go back if I were in the area.
They have the best healthy food. The crabcakes sandwich is delicious!!!!!
The meal was great, loved the homemade dressing and the crab cake was seasoned well. Only reason I'm not giving five stars is small portions for the cost.
Friendly dudes, delicious clean healthy food. Killer crab cakes. NOTE: google maps tells you it’s across the street from where it actually is! It’s in the bazaar
Creative cooking. We enjoyed their version of vegetarian gumbo.
Amazing crab cake po' boy! Incredible hospitality from Greg! He is awesome! Be sure to stop by and grab a bite when you are in the French Market.

Had a hard time finding healthy, vegan options until I found this place! The food was AMAZING, the staff was friendly and the place was clean. I will definitely be eating here again before I leave. You will not be disappointed.
love love love it!!!!

Exceeded my expectations. There's a bit of a wait to receive your food, but it's completely worth it. I had the gluten free pancakes, vegan eggs with cheese and vegan crabcake. Everything was beyond scrumptious.

Had the raspberry salad with wild caught salmon. DELICIOUS!

In a city without many vegan or vegetarian options, I was excited to try this place. I had a little trouble finding it because it's not really a restaurant, but rather a bar-like counter in an open-air food court. Very limited seating. The place was very busy at lunch and the staff a bit overwhelmed. My dish was a mixed bag. The steamed veggies were clearly frozen veggies simply reheated without any seasoning, but the black bean sandwich was really delicious. The server was the highlight of the experience. Super-friendly and attentive. I would recommend this place if you're looking for a quick and healthy bite, but be aware that it's a tight and busy lunch counter and doesn't have much ambience.
Good food and service

The best vegan, Gf and vegetarian food in New Orleans. The service was fast and the staff were friendly. The reason why I am rating this place a 4 is because they use too much plastic and disposable cutlery.

Absolutely outstanding service and food. An all around fantastic experience. Their apple patties are some of the best vegan foods I've ever had. The amount and quality of the vegan and gluten free options is amazing, and the staff are some of the nicest, friendliest people. This place is incredible.
They have great vegan and gluten free options. Everything was delicious, and the staff were super friendly! I'll be going back for sure :)
Kind of pricey, but worth it. Very tasty and full of flavor. Very sweet people!
My goodness! The food is delicious & the hospitality is amazing. This is our first meal here, but we know we’ll be back before we leave NOLA!! You’re missing out if you don’t stop here. #blackowned

Not only delicious, but GENUINELY SUPER FRIENDLY. Flavorful & healthy. it's hard to find great gluten free food (I got the gf okra gumbo & gf crabcake), but this place does it well. I'll be back for more!

Pro: Great food.  Con: Their customer service is lacking but it's a very busy place so I understand it's hard to keep up with everyone trying to order.  It took a while just to get a menu, like 15mins.

First place I ate last time we visited New Orleans. Traveling Celiac is not always easy and we were quite pleased with the tasty GF crab cake. This trip we opted to make Meals From the Heart out last stop before returning home. The experience was not as equally pleasurable. The crab cake was spot on however the menu knowledge, service and general experience were not consistent with our last visit. The server was not very helpful and wound up ringing my order in the way she felt necessary rather than listening and answering my questions. I wound up with a GF crab cake 7.99 + 1.00 GF charge accompanied by a small side of extremely water logged vegetables (4.99) Take your time to read the menu before ordering so you don't have to rely on the staffs knowledge.

Walk up restaurant with stools in open air French Market (which also offers areas with tables for all) that offers wonderful food. Staff is knowledgeable about gluten free, vegetarian, and vegan options. Everything is fresh and made per request. Very friendly and understanding employees! Highly recommend, esp if on a restrictive diet.
My Favorite Restaurant in New Orleans!!! (And I'm born & raise in here)
Healthy Cajun food in NOLA! Best crab cakes I've ever had. The owners and staff are super friendly. Healthy food full of flavor.
Wonderful! Delicious food and smiling, friendly proprietor. Definitely worth the wait.

Was worried I wouldn’t be able to experience all the great food NOLA has to offer as a vegetarian. The vegan gumbo is to die for and even my nonvegetarian friend agreed. Kind and helpful staff, I felt and tasted the love.
